           border: 1px solid black;\n                                      padding: 5px;\n                                      margin: 2px;\n                                      text-align: left;\n                                  }\n                                  .block\n                                         {\n                                         display:block;\n                                         }\n                                         .none\n                                         {\n                                         display:none;\n                                         }\n                    					 .btn-confirm\n                  					 {\n                    					 background-color:#26327e !important;\n                    					 margin-left:30% !important;\n                    					 color: white!important;\n                    					 border:none !important;\n                    					 width:40% !important;\n                    					 margin-top:5% !important;\n                    					 height:42px !important;\n                    					 }\n                                       .btn-cancel\n                                       {\n                                       background-color:#26327e !important;\n                    					 margin-left:30% !important;\n                    					 color: white!important;\n                    					 border:none !important;\n                    					 width:38% !important;\n                    					 margin-top:5% !important;\n                    					 height:42px !important;\n                                       }\n                  .marginLeft\n 				 {\n 				 margin-left:10px\n 				 }\n                                           </style>\n                                       </head>\n                                       <body style=\"background-repeat: repeat; -webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%; -ms-text-size-adjust: 100%; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;\">\n                                               <div class=\"contentEditableContainer contentTextEditable\">\n                                                   <div class=\"contentEditable\">\n                                                       <span>Dear @Model.FranchiseeName,</span>\n                                                       <br />\n                                                       <br />\n                                                       \n                                                    <p>\n                               In December, 2020 we informed you that we were moving to automate the annual document submission process in order to streamline the process.  If you have not already uploaded your documents, you will need to do so along with your next royalty submission (as we do with the annual report submission the first week of each year) \n 							  in order to submit your weekly.<br/>\n          						<br/>\n 								The required documents are as follows:<br/>\n 								1. Your Last Federal Tax Filings. <br/>\n 								2. Prior Year Financials  This includes the following:<br/>\n 								<div style=\'margin-left:20px\' class=\'marginLeft\'><p>     1. Profit & Loss Statement (Accrual) as of 12-31-2020  This can be created by running your QB P&L Statement as of 12-31-2020, then exporting as an excel sheet, \n 									 saving and uploading to the system.<br/>\n 									 2. Balance Sheet  (Accrual) as of 12-31-2020  This can be created by running your QB Balance Sheet Statement as of 12-31-2020, then exporting as an excel sheet, \n 									 saving and uploading to the system. <br/>\n 									 3. Material Purchases for 12-31-2020  This can be created by simply running your QB report for the calendar year, double clicking on your MATERIAL PURCHASE total, which will open a report of the records associated with this segment,\n 									 export to excel, and upload the excel sheet.<br/>\n 							  </p></div>  3. Current Certificate-of-Insurance (naming MARBLELIFE, INC as an also insured)<br/>\n 								4. Current Resale Certificate<br/>\n 							   How to upload your reports:<br/>	\n 							   The easiest way is to go to the DOCUMENTS tab within the royalty reporting system, select UPLOAD, find your file, and then select the appropriate file type from the dropdown matching the above sections.  You will be asked to assign these to the \n 							   appropriate year.  Your financials will be for 2020.  Your taxes will be for \n 							   the year they are being filed which could be 2019, 2020 or 2021 depending on\n 							   your extensions and fiscal year.  For most of us you will be uploading your 2019 taxes if you have filed an extension for 2020, or your 2020 if you have already submitted these.\n   							<br/>\n 							If you have a question  you can contact Laurie or Alan and we can walk you through the process.  We recommend collecting your documents together before calling.  If you have your documents saved on your system this is a very quick process.\n 							<br/>\n 							How do we use these documents: <br/>\n 							<div class=\"marginLeft\" style=\"margin-left:20px;\"><p>1. Tax Filings  To ensure your company has remembered to file your taxes (and in so doing avoid the \n 							damaging impact the IRS can have on your business.  As you have exclusive \n 							rights to your market, this also impacts MARBLELIFEs business and ability to \n 							service clients within your market.<br/>\n 							2.Financials  We routinely benchmark across the system in order to identify opportunities for improvement arise from identifying\n 							best-in-class within a cost management area AND areas of high cost where you may have an unknown opportunity to capture costs.  In the past we have been able to highlight \n 							opportunities for quick savings based on these comparisons.<br/>\n 							3. Materials  We seek to understand how much we are buying across the system to identify opportunities to bring in products that will benefit the system AND to identify area we can potentially reduce costs by leveraging across the system.\n 							</p></div><br/>\n 							4. Resale Certificate  Recent changes in state internet tax laws now requires that sales tax be collected on Franchise-Sourcing sales UNLESS you have provided us a copy of your RESELLERs Certificate.  This can represent a 6 to 8% increase in costs which are avoidable with this certificate. <br/>\n 							        <br/> <p class=\"marginLeft\">1. If you do NOT intend to submit one, upload a letter dated for the 2020 indicating you do NOT intend to submit a certificate and we should charge sales tax.\n 							        <br/> 2. If your state allows you to file in perpetuity with a single filing, simply re-upload your prior certificate (which is likely already in your document file, in which case you can download, resave and upload)\n 							        <br/> 3. For most of us, this means submitting your current certificate.</p>\n 							Your renewal fee is @Model.RenewableFees, and would need to received by @Model.RenewableDate.  We look forward to working and growing with you for another 10 years.\n                                                  </p>\n                 								 <br />\n                 								\n                   						 \n                    						 <br/>\n                                              <br/>\n                                   				Regards,\n                                                      \n                                                       <p>\n                                                         Alan Mayr<br />\n                                                         @Model.Base.CompanyName<sup>&reg;</sup> <br />\n                                       				  </p>\n                                                       \n                                                   </div>\n                                                </div>\n                                       </body>\n                                         </html>\n                   \n                  \n             \n                 \n            ' WHERE (`Id` = '43');


